<item>
            <title>[SOLR-8094] HdfsUpdateLog should not replay buffered documents as a replacement to dropping them.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-8094</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This can cause replicas to get out of sync because replication may have failed, but then if you replay you can setup peer sync to pass when it should not.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After talking to Yonik a bit, I tried doing everything the same as on local fs except skipping the truncate - because of error handling we already have, this appears to work.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
